    "description": "Grow your career with NABARD Capital India! We are hiring a Senior Financial Analyst for our Tiruchirappalli team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout NABARD Capital India:\nNABARD Capital India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NABARD Capital India!",
